PROJECT FLOW
================================================================================

Client (Postman/Browser)
        ↓  HTTP Request
   StudentController        <- handles the route (e.g. POST /students)
        ↓
   StudentService           <- business logic layer
        ↓
   StudentRepository        <- talks to the database (extends JpaRepository)
        ↓
   Hibernate (ORM)          <- converts Java <-> SQL automatically
        ↓
   MySQL (studentdb)        <- stores/retrieves data from `student` table
        ↑
   Student (model)          <- Java class that maps to the DB table

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

EACH LAYER'S RESPONSIBILITY:

Model      -> Student.java          -> defines data structure (id, name, age)
                                       maps to the DB table via @Entity

Repository -> StudentRepository.java -> interface, extends JpaRepository
                                        gives save(), findAll(), findById() for free
                                        no implementation needed

Service    -> StudentService.java   -> business logic layer
                                       sits between controller and repository

Controller -> StudentController.java -> receives HTTP requests
                                        calls service
                                        returns JSON response

Config     -> application.properties -> DB connection, port, JPA settings

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

EXAMPLE: POST /students  with {"id":1, "name":"Ravi", "age":21}

1. StudentController.createStudent() receives JSON -> converts to Student object
2. Calls service.createStudent(student)
3. Service calls repository.save(student)
4. Hibernate runs: INSERT INTO student (age, name, id) VALUES (21, 'Ravi', 1)
5. Record saved in MySQL -> returned as JSON back to client

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

HIBERNATE LOGS EXPLAINED:

select ... from student              -> GET /students       (findAll)
select ... from student where id=?   -> GET /students/{id}  (findById)
insert into student ...              -> POST /students       (save)
update student set ... where id=?    -> PUT /students/{id}   (save with existing id)
delete from student where id=?       -> DELETE /students/{id}(deleteById)

? = placeholder filled at runtime (prevents SQL injection)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

DEFAULT PORT: 8080 (set by embedded Tomcat)
To change: add  server.port=8081  in application.properties
